tton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528758\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528758\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 11, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104iyj1665702557441.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/iyj1665702557441.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/iyj1665702557441.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"iyj1665702557441\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      $typed\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"iyj1665702557441___typed_293134\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Explicitly convert data to a specified data type.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__topic_d90350e1_d90351e1_d90352e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__p_d90353e1_d90354e1_d90355e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">DataTypeConverter</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\")</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__p_d90356e1_d90357e1_d90358e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\")</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<div class=\"example\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">vBoolean = $typed(\"$boolean(01)\") ; returns F: value is string and begins with 0\nvNumber = $typed(\"$number(01)\") ; returns 1\nvString = $typed(\"$string(01)\") ; returns 01\nvString = $typed(\"01\") ; returns 01</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__topic_d60162e1_d60163e1_d60164e1_d60165e1_d60166e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1065400e106\">\n                       \n Parameters\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__li_d35783e1_d35784e1_d35785e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">DataTypeConverter</var>—defines the target data type to be used when converting the value. One of <code class=\"ph codeph\">$boolean</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">$clock</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">$date</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">$datim</code>, $float, <code class=\"ph codeph\">Snumber</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">$string</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">$syntax</code>. if omitted, <code class=\"ph codeph\">$string</code> is assumed.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__li_d35786e1_d35787e1_d35788e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>—data to be converted.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__topic_d60167e1_d60168e1_d60169e1_d60170e1_d60171e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1065400e152\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__p_d90365e1_d90366e1_d90367e1\">Converted data.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__topic_d60172e1_d60173e1_d60174e1_d60175e1_d60176e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1065400e162\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__d5916e20\">Allowed in all component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__topic_d60177e1_d60178e1_d60179e1_d60180e1_d60181e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1065400e171\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__p_d90377e1_d90378e1_d90379e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span> function is used to ensure that data values are interpreted as being of a specific data type. For many data types, there is an explicit ProcScript function that can be used to perform this conversion. However, for data types String, Float, and Boolean, the only way to enforce this conversion is using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span> function.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Data Type Conversion Functions</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__1\">Using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__2\">Type-specific ProcScript Function</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__3\">Returns</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$boolean(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__2\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__3\">Boolean </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$clock(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kbw1665702554427.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kbw1665702554427.html\" title=\"Return the system time or convert the argument to the Time data type.\">$clock</a>(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__3\">Time type </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$date(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qdt1718972098664.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qdt1718972098664.html\" title=\"Return the current date or convert the argument to the Date data type.\">$date</a>(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__3\">Date type </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$datim(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wvg1665702554514.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wvg1665702554514.html\" title=\"Return the system date and time, or convert the argument to the Datetime data type.\">$datim</a>(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__3\">DateTime type </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$float(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__2\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__3\">Float type</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$number(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mfg1718973151470.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mfg1718973151470.html\" title=\"Returns a numeric value derived from a numeric string.\">$number</a>(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__3\">Number type</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$string(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__2\">Although there is a\n\t\t\t\t <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$string</span> ProcScript function, it is used to convert XML entities to strings, not\n\t\t\t\t to convert data to String.</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__3\">Constant string type</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$syntax(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bqr1665702555238.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bqr1665702555238.html\" title=\"Convert a string to a syntax string.\">$syntax</a>(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__3\">Syntax string type</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$typed</code><code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$regex(</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tqa1714484099568.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tqa1714484099568.html\" title=\"Convert a string to a regex string.\">$regex</a>(</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1__entry__3\">Regex string type</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__p_d90380e1_d90381e1_d90382e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span> function (and other data type conversion functions) can be used to construct typed lists for use in passing lists of parameters. For example, the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate/list</span> command requires a typed list of parameters.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__topic_d60182e1_d60183e1_d60184e1_d60185e1_d60186e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1065400e521\">\n                       \n $string\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__p_d90386e1_d90387e1_d90388e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">$string</code> converter used in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span> should not be confused with <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$string</span> ProcScript function. They have a different purpose and different syntax:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9857e1_d9858e1_d9859e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\"></span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9857e1_d9858e1_d9859e1__entry__1\">\n ProcScript\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9857e1_d9858e1_d9859e1__entry__2\">\n Returns\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9857e1_d9858e1_d9859e1__entry__3\">\n Explanation\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9857e1_d9858e1_d9859e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$string</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"A &amp;amp; B\")</code></p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9857e1_d9858e1_d9859e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"A &amp; B\"</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9857e1_d9858e1_d9859e1__entry__3\">The parameter is a string that contains an XML\n                        entity <code class=\"ph codeph\">&amp;amp;</code>, which the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$string</span>\n                        ProcScript function converts to an ampersand (&amp;). </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9857e1_d9858e1_d9859e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$typed($string(\"A &amp;amp; B\"))</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9857e1_d9858e1_d9859e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"A &amp; B\"</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9857e1_d9858e1_d9859e1__entry__3\">\n The parameter is the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$string</span> ProcScript function, which converts the XML entity.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9857e1_d9858e1_d9859e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$typed(\"$string(A &amp;amp; B)\")</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9857e1_d9858e1_d9859e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"A &amp;amp; B\"</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9857e1_d9858e1_d9859e1__entry__3\">The parameter is a string containing the\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">$string</code> converter. It does not convert the XML entity,\n                        and just returns the literal string. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9857e1_d9858e1_d9859e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$typed(\"A &amp;amp; B\")</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9857e1_d9858e1_d9859e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"A &amp;amp; B\"</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"iyj1665702557441__table_d9857e1_d9858e1_d9859e1__entry__3\">The parameter is a string, so the default\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">$string</code> converter is assumed. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__section_ej4_hqj_1cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1065400e683\">Example: Typed List</h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">For example, the following code generates a list with different values\n               for <code class=\"ph codeph\">012345</code> depending on the data type:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"iyj1665702557441__pre_apb_3qj_1cc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">variables\n string vList\nendvariables\nputitem vList, -1, $typed(\"$string(012345)\")\nputitem vList, -1, $typed(\"$boolean(012345)\") ; start with 0 yields F\nputitem vList, -1, $typed(\"$boolean(12345)\") ; start with any other character yields T\nputitem vList, -1, $typed(\"$float(012345)\")\nputitem vList, -1, $number(012345)\nputitem vList, -1, $date(12-3-45) ; requires valid input string\nputitem vList, -1, $clock(012345)\n;Result: vList = 012345<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>F<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>T<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>12345<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>12345<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>20450312<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>0000000001234500</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528758\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528758\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$typed Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 11, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 $typed Explicitly convert data to a specified data type. $typed (\" DataTypeConverter ( Value ) \") $typed (\" Value \") vBoolean = $typed(\"$boolean(01)\") ; returns F: value is string and begins with 0 vNumber = $typed(\"$number(01)\") ; returns 1 vString = $typed(\"$string(01)\") ; returns 01 vString = $typed(\"01\") ; returns 01 Copy Parameters DataTypeConverter —defines the target data type to be used when converting the value. One of $boolean , $clock , $date , $datim , $float, Snumber , $string , $syntax . if omitted, $string is assumed. Value —data to be converted. Return Values Converted data. Use Allowed in all component types. Description The $typed function is used to ensure that data values are interpreted as being of a specific data type. For many data types, there is an explicit ProcScript function that can be used to perform this conversion. However, for data types String, Float, and Boolean, the only way to enforce this conversion is using the $typed function. Table 1. Data Type Conversion Functions Using $typed Type-specific ProcScript Function Returns $typed (\"$boolean( Value )\") Boolean $typed (\"$clock( Value )\") $clock ( Value ) Time type $typed (\"$date( Value )\") $date ( Value ) Date type $typed (\"$datim( Value )\") $datim ( Value ) DateTime type $typed (\"$float( Value )\") Float type $typed (\"$number( Value )\") $number ( Value ) Number type $typed (\"$string( Value )\") Although there is a $string ProcScript function, it is used to convert XML entities to strings, not to convert data to String. Constant string type $typed (\"$syntax( Value )\") $syntax ( Value ) Syntax string type $typed (\"$regex( Value )\") $regex ( Value ) Regex string type The $typed function (and other data type conversion functions) can be used to construct typed lists for use in passing lists of parameters. For example, the activate/list command requires a typed list of parameters. $string The $string converter used in $typed should not be confused with $string ProcScript function. They have a different purpose and different syntax: Table 2. ProcScript Returns Explanation $string (\"A &amp; B\") \"A & B\" The parameter is a string that contains an XML entity &amp; , which the $string ProcScript function converts to an ampersand (&). $typed($string(\"A &amp; B\")) \"A & B\" The parameter is the $string ProcScript function, which converts the XML entity. $typed(\"$string(A &amp; B)\") \"A &amp; B\" The parameter is a string containing the $string converter. It does not convert the XML entity, and just returns the literal string. $typed(\"A &amp; B\") \"A &amp; B\" The parameter is a string, so the default $string converter is assumed. Example: Typed List For example, the following code generates a list with different values for 012345 depending on the data type: variables string vList endvariables putitem vList, -1, $typed(\"$string(012345)\") putitem vList, -1, $typed(\"$boolean(012345)\") ; start with 0 yields F putitem vList, -1, $typed(\"$boolean(12345)\") ; start with any other character yields T putitem vList, -1, $typed(\"$float(012345)\") putitem vList, -1, $number(012345) putitem vList, -1, $date(12-3-45) ; requires valid input string putitem vList, -1, $clock(012345) ;Result: vList = 012345 ; F ; T ; 12345 ; 12345 ; 20450312 ; 0000000001234500 Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}